Test and Measurement Equipment Market - Competitive and Segmentation Analysis:

**Segments**

- On the basis of product, the global test and measurement equipment market can be segmented into general purpose test equipment (GPTE) and mechanical test equipment.
- Based on service, the market can be categorized into calibration services, repair services, and others.
- By end-user, the market is classified into automotive, aerospace & defense, IT & telecommunications, education & government, healthcare, industrial, and others.

**Market Players**

- Some of the key players operating in the global test and measurement equipment market include Rohde & Schwarz GmbH & Co., Yokogawa Electric Corporation, Fortive, Keysight Technologies, Anritsu, National Instruments, Teledyne Technologies, Advantest Corporation, EXFO, and VIAVI Solutions.

The global test and measurement equipment market is anticipated to witness significant growth during the forecast period of 2022 to 2029. Factors such as the increasing demand for high quality and reliable products across various industries including automotive, aerospace, telecommunications, and healthcare are driving the market growth. The need for efficient testing and measurement processes to ensure product quality, safety, and compliance with regulatory standards is further fueling the market expansion. Technological advancements such as the integration of Internet of Things (IoT) and artificial intelligence (AI) in test and measurement equipment are also contributing to the market growth.

The demand for general purpose test equipment (GPTE) is expected to remain high as it is widely used for a variety of electronic testing applications. Mechanical test equipment is also gaining traction due to the growing emphasis on mechanical properties testing in industries like automotive and aerospace. Calibration services play a crucial role in maintaining the accuracy and reliability of test and measurement equipment, thereby driving the service segment growth. End-users such as the automotive and aerospace sectors are investing heavily in test and measurement equipment to ensure the quality and performance of their products.

